---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Example Reconstruction | Prima Veritas">

<main class="flex-1">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="border-b border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
      <h1 class="font-sans text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-off-white leading-tight">
        Example Reconstruction
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-xl text-off-white/80">
        A concrete example of how a fragmented operational event history becomes a sealed, reproducible chain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


<!-- SCENARIO -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Scenario
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        A set of operational logs tracks updates to an order across multiple systems:
        order management, customer support, and fulfillment.
      </p>

      <p>
        Each system records events independently. Timestamps drift. Field formats differ.
        Identifiers are inconsistent. No single system preserves the full history.
      </p>

      <p>
        The result is a fragmented view of what actually happened.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- RAW INTAKE -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">

    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Raw intake
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-w-5xl text-sm text-off-white/80">

      <div>
        <strong>Order System</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          14:02:11 ORDER_7421 → CREATED<br/>
          14:05:33 ADDRESS UPDATED
        </code>
      </div>

      <div>
        <strong>Support Log</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          Ticket opened for order 7421<br/>
          Customer requested delivery change
        </code>
      </div>

      <div>
        <strong>Fulfillment Record</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          Shipment scheduled<br/>
          Delivery attempt recorded
        </code>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80">
      <strong>Observed Issues</strong>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-off-white/60">
        <li>Timestamp drift</li>
        <li>Non-uniform identifiers (ORDER_7421 vs 7421 vs free text)</li>
        <li>Missing cross-reference keys</li>
        <li>Events spread across unrelated systems</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>


<!-- CANONICAL EVENT ENVELOPE -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Canonical envelope normalization
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        Each raw record is transformed into a canonical envelope: unified timestamp,
        source identifier, schema version, and structured payload.
      </p>

      <code class="block mt-4 text-off-white/60">
{`{
  event_id: "e1032",
  source: "order.system",
  timestamp: "2026-04-12T14:02:11Z",
  payload: {
    order_id: "7421",
    status: "CREATED"
  }
}`}
      </code>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- EVENT CHAIN -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Event chain construction
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        Each envelope is hashed. The hash of the prior event is embedded in the next.
        Order is explicit. Mutation invalidates the sequence.
      </p>

      <code class="block mt-4 text-off-white/60">
{`e1032 → hash: a94f...
e1033 → prev_hash: a94f...
e1034 → prev_hash: b221...`}
      </code>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- RECONSTRUCTION -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Deterministic reconstruction
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        From the ordered chain, system state at any point in time can be reconstructed.
      </p>

      <p>
        Order creation, address changes, support intervention, and delivery attempts
        are derived from a single unified history.
      </p>

      <p>
        Given the same input chain, reconstruction output is identical across environments.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- VERIFICATION -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Independent verification
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        The final bundle contains the full event sequence and hash lineage.
      </p>

      <p>
        A third party can validate structural integrity and ordering without access
        to the original systems.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- RUN YOUR OWN RECONSTRUCTION -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">

    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Run Your Own Reconstruction
    </h2>

    <p class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80">
      Upload a dataset and generate a verifiable artifact using the same deterministic pipeline.
    </p>

    <!-- UPLOAD -->
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-6">

      <input type="file"
             accept=".csv"
             class="bg-charcoal border border-white/10 text-off-white text-sm px-4 py-2" />

      <button class="bg-carbon-navy font-semibold text-sm border border-white/20 px-4 py-2 opacity-60 cursor-not-allowed">
        Generate Artifact (backend not connected)
      </button>

      <a href="#"
         class="nav-link text-sm opacity-75 hover:text-[var(--accent)]">
         Download Sample CSV →
      </a>

    </div>

    <!-- FILE REQUIREMENTS -->
    <div class="mt-10 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">

      <div>
        <strong>File Requirements</strong>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-off-white/60">
          <li>CSV format</li>
          <li>Timestamped events</li>
          <li>Up to 5MB per upload</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <details class="text-off-white/70">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer">View Full Format Requirements</summary>

        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-off-white/60">

          <p><strong>Required header (exact order):</strong><br/>
          timestamp,stream_id,event_type,actor,object,notes</p>

          <p><strong>Rules:</strong><br/>
          ISO 8601 timestamps required<br/>
          Timestamp must include timezone<br/>
          Example: 2026-01-15T14:22:00Z<br/>
          No extra columns<br/>
          No missing columns<br/>
          Max file size: 5MB<br/>
          Max rows: 50,000</p>

        </div>

      </details>

      <p>
        Prima Veritas does not modify or infer missing data. Inputs must match the required format
        to ensure deterministic, reproducible results.
      </p>

      <p>
        Do not upload sensitive or personal data. Files are processed for demonstration purposes only.
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- SUCCESS PLACEHOLDER -->
    <div class="mt-10 border border-white/10 p-6 text-sm text-off-white/70 opacity-60">
      Artifact Generated Successfully (placeholder)<br/>
      Artifact Hash: —<br/>
      Event Count: —<br/>
      Preview: (backend not connected)
    </div>

  </div>
</section>


</main>

</Layout>